<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Happiness" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Happiness,</orth> 1) good luck, good fortune: <cit><quote>all h. bechance to thee in Milan,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 1, 61</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>bring you back in h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 1, 75</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a dear h. to women,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 129</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>envy no man's h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.79" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 79</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the victory fell on us. Great h.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 2, 58</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and lo, the h.! go and importune her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 108</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Caesar will unstate his h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 30</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.379" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 379</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.41" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 76</bibl> (cf. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 76</bibl>). <bibl n="shak. per 2.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 3, 11</bibl>. Used as a form of good wishes, especially in meeting and parting: <cit><quote>good day and h.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 30</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>health and h. betide my liege,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.91" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 91</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.81" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.227" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 227</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 124</bibl>. <cit><quote>h. to his accomplices,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 2, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>all h. unto my lord,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 93</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.6.6" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 6, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 2, 46</bibl>. <cit><quote>h. to their sheets!</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 29</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.5.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 5, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 60</bibl>. <cit><quote>the best of h. keep with you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.234" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 234</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) content, felicity: Lucr. Dedic. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.234" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 234</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 22" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.183" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 183</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.173" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 173</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 2, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.117" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 2, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.209" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 209</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.3.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.119" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.119" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 119</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.119" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 119</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 64</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.20" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.6.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 6, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.2.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 2, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.290" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 290</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 24</bibl>. <cit><quote>she shall be to the h. of England an aged princess,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 5, 57</bibl></cit>. == that which causes content, makes happy: <cit><quote>society is the h. of life,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.168" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 168</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>queen Margaret, England's h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.37" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 37</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) propriety, goodliness: <cit><quote>he hath indeed a good outward h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 191</bibl></cit> (== a happy exterior, a prepossessing appearance). <cit><quote>how pregnant his replies are! a h. that often madness hits on,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 213</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.185" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 185</bibl>.
